Big 12 investigates reports of anti-Mormon chants during OSU-BYU basketball game

by: Mario Gonzalez/KFOR

Posted: Feb 5, 2026 / 03:38 PM CST

Updated: Feb 5, 2026 / 03:38 PM CST

by: Mario Gonzalez/KFOR

Posted: Feb 5, 2026 / 03:38 PM CST

Updated: Feb 5, 2026 / 03:38 PM CST

SHARE

STILLWATER, Okla. (KFOR) â The Big 12 Conference is investigating reports of ‘inappropriate chants’ during Oklahoma State’s men’s basketball team’s win on Wednesday night against No. 16 BYU.

The OSU men’s basketball team and fans are riding high after the big win over the Cougars, 99-92. After the game was over, OSU fans stormed the court; however, controversy later filled the air over the game due to reported anti-Mormon chants that came from the Oklahoma State student section during the game.

Cowboys Upset #16 BYU

Big 12 Commissioner Brett Yormark released a statement on Thursday after reports of the anti-Mormon chants that were heard.

Following Wednesday night’s game, BYU coach Kevin Young shared frustration after hearing “F The Mormons” chants.
